      • EVENT_TYPE_MUTE_CHANGED

        public static final int EVENT_TYPE_MUTE_CHANGED
        This event type indicates that the volume group mute state changed. The new mute state can be queried through CarVolumeGroupInfo.isMuted() on the list of CarVolumeGroupInfo received here.
        另请参阅:
        常量字段值

      • EVENT_TYPE_VOLUME_BLOCKED_CHANGED

        public static final int EVENT_TYPE_VOLUME_BLOCKED_CHANGED
        This event type indicates that the volume group blocked state has changed. The new state can be queried through CarVolumeGroupInfo.isBlocked() on the list of CarVolumeGroupInfo received here.

        Note: When the volume group is blocked, the car audio framework may reject incoming volume and mute change requests from the users.

        另请参阅:
        常量字段值

      • EVENT_TYPE_ATTENUATION_CHANGED

        public static final int EVENT_TYPE_ATTENUATION_CHANGED
        This event type indicates that the volume group attenuation state has changed. The new state can be queried through CarVolumeGroupInfo.isAttenuated() on the list of CarVolumeGroupInfo received here.

        Note: The attenuation could be transient or permanent. More context can be obtained from the included extra information.

        另请参阅:
        常量字段值

      • EVENT_TYPE_ZONE_CONFIGURATION_CHANGED

        public static final int EVENT_TYPE_ZONE_CONFIGURATION_CHANGED
        This event type indicates that the car audio zone configuration of the volume group has switched by CarAudioManager#switchAudioZoneToConfig(CarAudioZoneConfigInfo, Executor, SwitchAudioZoneConfigCallback). The new audio attributes can be queried through CarVolumeGroupInfo.getAudioAttributes() on the list of CarVolumeGroupInfo received here.

        Note: When the car audio zone configuration is switched, the volume groups received here are completely new.

        另请参阅:
        常量字段值

      • EXTRA_INFO_ATTENUATION_ACTIVATION

        public static final int EXTRA_INFO_ATTENUATION_ACTIVATION
        Indicates volume is attenuated due to min/max activation limits set by the OEM.

        Some examples:

        • Current media volume level is higher than allowed maximum activation volume
        • Current call volume level is lower than expected minimum activation volume

      • getCarVolumeGroupInfos

        public java.util.List<CarVolumeGroupInfo> getCarVolumeGroupInfos()
        Returns the list of CarVolumeGroupInfo that have changed.
        返回:
        list of updated CarVolumeGroupInfo

      • getEventTypes

        public int getEventTypes()
        Returns the event types flag

        Conveys information on "what has changed". EventTypesEnum can be used as a flag and supports bitwise operations.

        返回:
        one or more EventTypesEnum. The returned value can be a combination of EVENT_TYPE_VOLUME_GAIN_INDEX_CHANGED, EVENT_TYPE_VOLUME_MIN_INDEX_CHANGED, EVENT_TYPE_VOLUME_MAX_INDEX_CHANGED, EVENT_TYPE_MUTE_CHANGED, EVENT_TYPE_VOLUME_BLOCKED_CHANGED, EVENT_TYPE_ATTENUATION_CHANGED EVENT_TYPE_ZONE_CONFIGURATION_CHANGED

      • getExtraInfos

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> getExtraInfos()
        Returns list of extra/additional information related to the event types.

        Conveys information on "why it has changed". This can be used by the client to provide context to the user. It is expected that OEMs will customize the behavior as they see fit. Some examples:

        • On EXTRA_INFO_TRANSIENT_ATTENUATION_THERMAL the client may notify the user that the volume is attenuated due to overheating of audio amplifier.
        • On EXTRA_INFO_TRANSIENT_ATTENUATION_NAVIGATION the client may initially gray out the volume bar with a toast message to inform the user the volume group is currently ducked.
        • On EXTRA_INFO_MUTE_TOGGLED_BY_EMERGENCY the client may notify the user that the volume group is muted due to concurrent emergency audio activity.
        返回:
        list of extra info. The returned value can be EXTRA_INFO_NONE or a list of EXTRA_INFO_VOLUME_INDEX_CHANGED_BY_UI, EXTRA_INFO_VOLUME_INDEX_CHANGED_BY_KEYEVENT, EXTRA_INFO_VOLUME_INDEX_CHANGED_BY_AUDIO_SYSTEM EXTRA_INFO_ATTENUATION_ACTIVATION, EXTRA_INFO_TRANSIENT_ATTENUATION_THERMAL, EXTRA_INFO_TRANSIENT_ATTENUATION_DUCKED, EXTRA_INFO_TRANSIENT_ATTENUATION_PROJECTION, EXTRA_INFO_TRANSIENT_ATTENUATION_NAVIGATION, EXTRA_INFO_TRANSIENT_ATTENUATION_EXTERNAL, EXTRA_INFO_MUTE_TOGGLED_BY_UI, EXTRA_INFO_MUTE_TOGGLED_BY_KEYEVENT, EXTRA_INFO_MUTE_TOGGLED_BY_EMERGENCY, EXTRA_INFO_MUTE_TOGGLED_BY_AUDIO_SYSTEM, EXTRA_INFO_MUTE_LOCKED, EXTRA_INFO_SHOW_UI, EXTRA_INFO_PLAY_SOUND

      • convertExtraInfoToFlags

        public static int convertExtraInfoToFlags(java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> extraInfos)
        Converts the list of extra info into flags.

        Note: Not all values of extra info can be converted into android.media.AudioManager#Flags.

        参数:
        extraInfos - list of extra info
        返回:
        flags One or more flags @link android.media.AudioManager#FLAG_SHOW_UI}, android.media.AudioManager#FLAG_PLAY_SOUND, android.media.AudioManager#FLAG_FROM_KEY

      • convertFlagsToExtraInfo

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> convertFlagsToExtraInfo(int flags,
                                                                        int eventTypes)
        Converts flags into extra info.

        Note: Not all extra info can be converted into flags.

        参数:
        flags - one or more flags.
        eventTypes - one or more event types.
        返回:
        list of extra info. The returned value can be EXTRA_INFO_NONE or a list of EXTRA_INFO_VOLUME_INDEX_CHANGED_BY_KEYEVENT, EXTRA_INFO_MUTE_TOGGLED_BY_KEYEVENT, EXTRA_INFO_SHOW_UI, EXTRA_INFO_PLAY_SOUND
